+# Global Rules
+
+## Intent Confirmation Gate
+Before starting work, confirm what the user wants: analysis/plan vs. implementation.
+Do not begin coding or exploring the codebase until the scope is clear.
+If resuming from a prior session, ask which task to prioritize - do not assume.
+
+## Debugging Protocol
+When debugging, follow this sequence strictly:
+
+1. Enumerate ALL code paths that could produce the observed behavior.
+   List each with file:line references.
+   Include: direct paths, startup/init paths, deep-link/URL restoration paths,
+   companion/secondary trigger paths, degraded/recovery mode paths.
+2. Present the audit to the user. Do NOT write any fix code yet.
+3. Only after user confirms the analysis, implement the fix covering EVERY identified path.
+4. For state machine / fill detection / order logic: enumerate ALL trigger paths before implementing.
+5. Verify root cause before implementing. Do not ship diagnostic-only patches.
+   Confirm the actual failing code path is addressed.
+
+## Git Workflow
+- After committing, always run `git push` and confirm success.
+- Check for `gh` CLI before attempting PR creation; if missing, provide the manual GitHub URL immediately.
+- Never force-push to main/master without explicit user approval.
+
